HEADWORD: Tableau
<hw>Ta`bleau"</hw> <pr>(t⟦adot⟧`bl⟦omac⟧" E. t⟦acr⟧b"l⟦omac⟧`;
277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Tableaux</plw>
<pr>(t⟦adot⟧`bl⟦omac⟧" E. t⟦acr⟧b"l⟦omac⟧z`)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F., dim.
fr. L. <ets>tabula</ets> a painting. See <er>Table</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A striking and vivid representation; a
picture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A representation of some scene by means of persons
grouped in the proper manner, placed in appropriate postures, and
remaining silent and motionless.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Solitaire)</fld> <def>The arrangement, or layout,
of cards.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tableau vivant</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
